haracter and circumstance. Good lives, according to Kekes, depend equally on pursuing possibilities that these conditions establish and on setting limits to their violations.Attempts to make political arrangements reflect these basic tenets of conservatism are unavoidably imperfect. Kekes concludes, however, that they represent a better hope for the future than any other possibility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aConservatismxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aConservatism. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172188540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501721885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501721885/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles